The beloved cartoon character Master Q (AKA: Lo Fu Ji) gets a hilarious live-action adaptation in the side-splitting comic adventure Mr. Funny-Bone! Join Master Q for a series of comic vignettes as he attempts to win the heart of the lovely Li Jing.
 Along for the ride is Master Q's loyal sidekick Potato, a stout fellow who's forever getting into silly mishaps. The pair get involved in plenty of shenanigans and gags, including pratfalls, low-brow bathroom humor, and even some fun fighting sequences.
 The Master Q adventures in Mr. Funny-Bone proved so popular that a later sequel, Mr. Funny-Bone Strikes Again was produced, and New Wave filmmaker Tsui Hark brought the series into the twenty-first century with a live-action/computer graphics hybrid called Master Q 2001.
 In any incarnation, the exploits of Master Q and Potato remain fundamentally the same. They're all full of slapstick fun, innately enjoyable laughs, and plenty of entertainment suitable for the whole family!
